WEBVTT

00:05.006 --> 00:08.384
[Maria] <i>It was a week since I broke up </i>
<i>with Scott, and I was doing great.</i>

00:08.468 --> 00:11.763
<i>I was throwing myself into exercise </i>
<i>and healthy living. I was doing great!</i>

00:11.846 --> 00:13.223
See?

00:13.306 --> 00:16.476
Sweating and jumping.
This is what people do after a breakup.

00:16.559 --> 00:17.644
Absolutely.

00:17.727 --> 00:19.687
Ever since I accepted
that Barbara's gone for good,

00:19.812 --> 00:21.439
I started turning over a new leaf.

00:21.522 --> 00:24.484
Yeah, I mean...
So, you feel better with exercise, right?

00:24.567 --> 00:27.070
Oh, absolutely.
Plus these great owl tranquilizers

00:27.153 --> 00:29.113
I got online
from this guy named Johnny He.

00:29.197 --> 00:31.491
[upbeat music playing]

00:31.574 --> 00:32.408
[hooting]

00:32.909 --> 00:35.662
-I'm high, like, literally 20 hours a day.
-Oh!

00:35.745 --> 00:37.288
Plus, the gym is a wonderful place

00:37.372 --> 00:38.414
to meet people. Truly.

00:38.498 --> 00:40.333
[chuckles] Hi, there.

00:40.416 --> 00:42.210
Hey, here's the big honeypot, girls.

00:42.293 --> 00:44.420
Where's all my female honeybees?

00:44.504 --> 00:46.589
[Maria chuckles] Well, I'm excited.

00:46.673 --> 00:49.634
You know, 'cause finally
I can get to do the things

00:49.717 --> 00:52.553
I've been putting off because
I was in a relationship.

00:52.637 --> 00:53.721
-You know.
-Yeah.

00:53.805 --> 00:56.558
Just going to salsa clubs alone or...

00:56.641 --> 00:58.810
going to a cat show alone.

00:58.893 --> 01:01.938
Acknowledging the homeless,
on a regular basis, you know.

01:02.021 --> 01:04.732
-Embroidery, it's so beautiful.
-Mmm.

01:04.816 --> 01:09.112
And I've always longed
to be interested to do it, so...

01:09.195 --> 01:12.031
But those are things you don't do
if you're tied down.

01:12.115 --> 01:14.158
Absolutely.
I love everything you're saying.

01:14.242 --> 01:18.329
But it's probably because I can only hear
the blood rushing in and out of my aorta.

01:18.413 --> 01:20.206
Did I mention there's a little man
living inside my brain?

01:21.332 --> 01:22.750
-His name is Danny.
-[gasps]

01:22.834 --> 01:24.294
-Owl drink?
-[hooting]

01:25.503 --> 01:28.256
Bruce, are you sure you're in a condition
to handle my career?

01:28.339 --> 01:30.967
-Let me check with Danny.
-[bells chiming]

01:31.050 --> 01:32.135
Answer is, "Yes."

01:32.218 --> 01:34.095
As a matter of fact, the Abluvia people

01:34.178 --> 01:37.348
are looking for a new pitch woman
for their brand-new campaign.

01:37.432 --> 01:39.475
Oh, Abluvia? Is that... yogurt?

01:39.559 --> 01:42.145
Yeah, a delicious yogurt
with herpes at the bottom.

01:42.228 --> 01:43.354
That's disgusting.

01:43.438 --> 01:44.731
No. Just joshing.

01:44.814 --> 01:45.815
[chuckles]

01:45.898 --> 01:48.401
Abluvia is a medicine for people
with mouth herpes.

01:48.484 --> 01:51.487
Speaking of herpes, that chick
over there is checking me out.

01:51.571 --> 01:52.655
I'm gonna give her something

01:52.739 --> 01:54.407
-to really look at. Come with me.
-Okay.

01:54.490 --> 01:56.242
-Oh. Okay.
-Just help me...

01:56.326 --> 01:58.036
-...pull down these cables, okay?
-Yes. Okay.

01:58.119 --> 01:59.871
I wanna get the full extension.

01:59.954 --> 02:01.497
Okay. [chuckles]

02:01.581 --> 02:04.500
You know, love really is
like a child's prison.

02:04.584 --> 02:05.710
You hold on tightly

02:05.793 --> 02:08.003
and then you let go lightly.

02:08.086 --> 02:09.714
-Okay. [gasps]
-Wait a second!

02:09.797 --> 02:11.424
-[bones snapping]
-[screaming]

02:12.175 --> 02:14.177
[theme music playing]

02:16.000 --> 02:22.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:35.782 --> 02:37.825
[Maria] <i>I'm a pterodactyl.</i>

02:43.831 --> 02:46.334
[Scott] I don't understand
what I did to her.

02:46.417 --> 02:49.462
I mean, why isn't Maria taking my calls
or calling me back?

02:49.545 --> 02:51.964
Yeah, well, it's really hard
to understand Maria,

02:52.048 --> 02:53.674
you know, most of the time--

02:53.758 --> 02:55.968
She thinks you fingerbanged her
in the kitchen on Thanksgiving.

02:56.052 --> 02:57.887
-Fingerbang?
-Mmm-hmm.

02:57.970 --> 03:00.598
Why have I heard nothing
of this tale of fingerbangery?

03:00.681 --> 03:02.558
Because you're a third-tier friend
at best.

03:02.642 --> 03:06.312
Wait. I promise you,
I did not fingerbang anyone.

03:06.437 --> 03:08.856
And she did not like
how you scraped half your plate.

03:08.940 --> 03:10.066
Mmm.

03:10.149 --> 03:12.985
Okay, was it the plate scrape
or was it the fingerbang?

03:13.069 --> 03:14.612
So you did fingerbang her.

03:15.279 --> 03:17.240
See, I'm part Native American, so...

03:17.323 --> 03:19.283
my people are used to being raped
at Thanksgiving.

03:19.367 --> 03:21.035
-Look. I have big hands.
-Ew.

03:21.119 --> 03:22.703
If I'd have fingerbanged her
in the kitchen,

03:22.787 --> 03:24.205
you'd have felt it in the living room.

03:24.288 --> 03:25.748
Okay, I don't feel safe!

03:25.832 --> 03:28.000
Look, fuck-knuckles,
Maria's got a mind of her own

03:28.084 --> 03:29.836
underneath all that yellow hair.

03:29.919 --> 03:31.712
So, do you want my advice?

03:31.796 --> 03:33.714
-Yes.
-You gotta go see her.

03:33.798 --> 03:36.884
Bring her something she likes,
like one of those self-help workbooks.

03:36.968 --> 03:38.302
-[mouthing indistinctly]
-She loves those things.

03:38.386 --> 03:39.762
She loves checking 'em off.

03:39.846 --> 03:41.472
She can feel herself getting better.

03:41.556 --> 03:44.976
Then you could bring her
a case of LaCroix sparkling water.

03:45.059 --> 03:46.269
Don't bring her that <i>pamplemousse</i> shit.

03:46.352 --> 03:47.645
That's fucking disgusting.

03:47.729 --> 03:50.440
Oh, you know what?
And get her some pug shit.

03:50.523 --> 03:51.983
She loves those little fuckers.

03:52.066 --> 03:53.151
Great.

03:53.234 --> 03:56.028
Thanks, but if you talk to her,
tell her that I'll do anything,

03:56.112 --> 03:57.905
whatever it takes
to make this right, okay?

03:57.989 --> 03:59.198
You should have thought about that

03:59.282 --> 04:01.325
before you fingered
your relationship to death.

04:01.409 --> 04:02.785
That's not what happened.

04:02.869 --> 04:05.455
Don't you point that
rape stick at me, man.

04:07.498 --> 04:08.583
Thank you.

04:11.544 --> 04:13.588
I don't feel safe with him anymore.

04:13.671 --> 04:16.591
Yeah, well, you shouldn't
feel safe around me either.

04:16.673 --> 04:17.925
Oh, God!

04:18.968 --> 04:20.595
[shrieking]

04:24.849 --> 04:25.808
[knocking]

04:31.647 --> 04:32.815
Oh, uh...

04:32.899 --> 04:33.941
Hey, Bert.

04:34.859 --> 04:35.902
Maria around?

04:35.985 --> 04:37.236
[Bert] It's late, Scott.

04:37.320 --> 04:39.989
And she doesn't want to see
your fucking garbage face.

04:40.072 --> 04:41.199
I don't get it.

04:42.658 --> 04:43.743
What did I do?

04:44.911 --> 04:46.704
Is this about the plate scrape
at Thanksgiving?

04:46.788 --> 04:49.999
[Bert] It's not my place to say.
But, yes, it was.

04:50.082 --> 04:52.877
And the fingerbang, and some other things.

04:52.960 --> 04:55.421
Among them, your general neediness.

04:55.505 --> 04:57.882
-[Blueberry] Who is it, Bert? It's late.
-[growling]

04:57.965 --> 04:59.509
Hey, Bert! Dude, that's not cool!

05:00.593 --> 05:02.762
[Bert] No, I wasn't going to hit her.

05:02.845 --> 05:06.015
In dog language it means,
"I love you. See you in bed."

05:06.098 --> 05:08.226
But I think it's fucked up
that you went there.

05:08.309 --> 05:09.352
Good night, Scott.

05:09.435 --> 05:11.437
Let me talk to her for one minute.

05:11.521 --> 05:13.773
[Bert barks] In dog years
that is four days,

05:13.856 --> 05:15.483
and that is fucking ridiculous.

05:15.566 --> 05:17.193
-Good night.
-No, look, please...

05:17.276 --> 05:19.612
-No, tell her... I love her.
-[door slams]

05:19.695 --> 05:20.696
[sighs]

05:24.575 --> 05:25.576
[Bert] Leave the clock.

05:26.661 --> 05:27.954
Leave the fucking clock!

05:32.208 --> 05:33.376
[door slams]

05:36.837 --> 05:38.673
Good job-job, Bert.

05:38.756 --> 05:41.342
[Bert] You're welcome.
My dear Maria, Scott loves you.

05:41.425 --> 05:43.678
-Why won't you talk to him?
-Because...

05:43.761 --> 05:47.348
I'm not comfortable with people,
places, or things needing me.

05:47.431 --> 05:49.892
When things need me, I let them down.

05:49.976 --> 05:52.853
Scott needs me. I'll let him down.

05:52.937 --> 05:55.982
[Bert] I need you.
And you've never let me down.

05:56.065 --> 05:58.401
That's not true, and you know it.

05:58.484 --> 06:01.404
[Bert] Oh, yes, there was that one time...

06:03.656 --> 06:05.116
[Maria] <i>I had been in Duluth</i>
<i>for six months,</i>

06:05.199 --> 06:07.785
<i>and I realized Los Angeles</i>
<i>wasn't my home anymore.</i>

06:07.868 --> 06:09.120
<i>This was where I belonged.</i>

06:09.203 --> 06:11.205
[Maria] Mom,
I was wondering if, maybe,

06:11.289 --> 06:13.374
I could have my own space
inside my room--

06:13.457 --> 06:16.002
[Marilyn] No, we don't want you
to isolate yourself...

06:16.085 --> 06:17.628
-[Maria] Okay.
-'cause we want...

06:17.712 --> 06:19.922
-some family time with you.
-[Maria] Okay.

06:20.006 --> 06:22.425
[Marilyn] You know what I mean?
[Maria] Yeah.

06:22.508 --> 06:24.552
There's a fine line
between isolation--

06:25.720 --> 06:28.264
-What! Where's Bert?
-[Joel] Where'd he go?

06:28.347 --> 06:30.391
He was just here, snorting away.

06:30.474 --> 06:31.517
[Maria] He's gone!

06:31.601 --> 06:33.019
[Marilyn] Let's don't get in a panic.

06:33.102 --> 06:35.187
-I mean, how far can a pug go?
-[Joel] Exactly.

06:35.313 --> 06:37.982
[screaming] Checklist stole another one
of my pugs!

06:38.065 --> 06:41.444
-It's Blossom all over again!
-[Marilyn] Bert?

06:43.112 --> 06:45.656
-Bert!
-Where could that pug have gone?

06:45.740 --> 06:46.866
Bert!

06:48.784 --> 06:49.952
[dog barking]

06:50.036 --> 06:51.287
[horse neighing]

06:51.370 --> 06:52.496
[Maria] Hi.

06:52.580 --> 06:56.167
I was wondering if I could put up
a flyer for my beloved, missing dog, Bert?

06:56.250 --> 06:57.460
Oh, sure.

06:57.543 --> 06:59.795
If you want, you can put one
in the break room, too.

06:59.879 --> 07:01.964
[Maria] Thank you so much. All right.

07:03.883 --> 07:07.261
Oh, I can't even look in the cages,
all these sad little eyes.

07:08.346 --> 07:10.473
Wait... Bert?

07:11.265 --> 07:13.601
[Bert] 'Tis I. I couldn't resist

07:13.684 --> 07:16.687
the pull of my true love.
[kisses] Lady pug.

07:16.812 --> 07:20.399
Better to die on one's paws
than live on one's haunches.

07:20.483 --> 07:21.901
It's you!

07:21.984 --> 07:25.071
It's him!
[stuttering] My dog, Bert, he--

07:25.154 --> 07:26.238
You're not dead!

07:26.322 --> 07:28.282
[Bert] I've never felt more alive.

07:28.366 --> 07:29.659
Bert, you ready to go home?

07:29.742 --> 07:31.202
[Bert] Not without my lover.

07:31.285 --> 07:32.370
Oh!

07:32.453 --> 07:33.663
[Bert] This is my lover.

07:33.746 --> 07:38.250
Bert, we can't take in another dog.
I can't be trusted.

07:38.334 --> 07:39.961
I killed Blossom.

07:40.044 --> 07:42.588
I can't take responsibility
for another dog.

07:42.672 --> 07:44.757
Except you,
you've been grandfathered in.

07:51.305 --> 07:53.015
-Blossom!
-[Blossom] That's right.

07:53.099 --> 07:55.351
Take a seat, bitch. And listen hard.

07:55.434 --> 07:57.728
[whimsical music playing]

07:59.981 --> 08:01.649
[Blossom singing]
<i>♪ A wet snout in your crotch ♪</i>

08:01.732 --> 08:02.984
<i>♪ Loose fur on your couch ♪</i>

08:03.067 --> 08:05.861
<i>♪ Sweet slobber on your cheek</i>
<i>A warm companion when you sleep ♪</i>

08:05.945 --> 08:10.825
<i>♪ Yes, puppies are the answer</i>
<i>The opposite of cancer ♪</i>

08:10.908 --> 08:12.159
[barks]

08:12.243 --> 08:14.078
[yawns]

08:14.161 --> 08:16.664
<i>♪ We watch you when you shit</i>
<i>We're really into it ♪</i>

08:16.747 --> 08:19.125
<i>♪ When we chase after cars</i>
<i>And dig up your yards ♪</i>

08:19.208 --> 08:24.213
<i>♪ You love us just the same</i>
<i>We don't even know our names ♪</i>

08:24.296 --> 08:26.590
<i>♪ Puppy, puppy, puppy ♪</i>

08:26.674 --> 08:28.718
<i>♪ Life getting scarier?</i>
<i>Just get a terrier ♪</i>

08:28.801 --> 08:31.178
<i>♪ Get beat by a brute?</i>
<i>Pick up a malamute ♪</i>

08:31.262 --> 08:33.722
<i>♪ Doubt the presence of God?</i>
<i>Get a shepherding dog ♪</i>

08:33.806 --> 08:34.807
<i>♪ Too much evil?</i>
<i>Get a beagle ♪</i>

08:34.890 --> 08:36.392
<i>♪ Lost your noodle?</i>
<i>Get a poodle ♪</i>

08:36.475 --> 08:38.561
<i>♪ Need a great big hug? ♪</i>

08:38.644 --> 08:41.938
<i>♪ Just get yourself a pug ♪</i>

08:44.025 --> 08:47.028
Really, dear.
Get yourself a pug.

08:48.696 --> 08:51.991
Oh, Blossom.
I'm so sorry I killed you.

08:52.074 --> 08:57.329
I was so stupid to turn over
the garbage can with all those pills,

08:57.413 --> 09:00.041
and I'm never gonna do that
to another dog again.

09:00.124 --> 09:01.709
Because I'm never gonna
have another dog,

09:01.792 --> 09:03.878
except for Bert, he's grandfathered in.

09:03.961 --> 09:05.087
[Blossom] Poor Maria.

09:05.171 --> 09:07.840
Don't you know, baby girl,
that if you hadn't killed me,

09:07.923 --> 09:09.050
I would have killed you?

09:09.759 --> 09:12.595
One of us was
not getting out of there alive.

09:12.678 --> 09:16.140
I admire you, actually.
You did what I could not.

09:16.223 --> 09:18.601
My paws were too tiny to pull the trigger.

09:18.684 --> 09:19.977
You had a gun?

09:20.061 --> 09:21.896
Of course. A Walther PPK.

09:22.688 --> 09:24.690
With a mother of pearl handle
and nickel plating.

09:24.774 --> 09:26.525
A lady pistol.

09:26.609 --> 09:28.986
I waited for you for hours to kill you.

09:29.070 --> 09:30.821
You did?

09:30.905 --> 09:34.408
But I had to make sissy and got distracted
by that delicious trash.

09:34.492 --> 09:35.534
Oh.

09:35.618 --> 09:38.496
Little did I know, you would be
making sissy all over my face.

09:39.246 --> 09:42.374
If you had gone first,
I would have eaten you from the ankles up.

09:42.458 --> 09:45.169
The best woman won.
My bowler hat is off to you.

09:45.795 --> 09:48.798
Wait. Are you forgiving me?

09:48.881 --> 09:50.257
Not quite yet, human.

09:50.341 --> 09:52.843
Not until you return
to the scum-filled streets

09:52.927 --> 09:55.054
of the City of Angels where you belong.

09:55.137 --> 09:59.433
But I'm worried if I went back to LA...
[stuttering] I'd go mad.

09:59.558 --> 10:02.853
And I wouldn't be able to handle it,

10:02.937 --> 10:05.481
and I'd go crazy on the 405.

10:05.564 --> 10:07.775
[Blossom] Fuck the 405. Take Coldwater.

10:07.858 --> 10:11.737
Look, Maria, if you put fear behind you
and live life to the fullest,

10:11.821 --> 10:14.031
our karmic debt will be repaid,

10:14.115 --> 10:16.742
and you will no longer be my murderer.

10:16.826 --> 10:19.328
Do what I can no longer do, Maria. Live!

10:19.411 --> 10:21.288
Live, <i>mein liebchen!</i>

10:21.372 --> 10:23.499
Goodbye, my sweet Maria.<i> Adieu.</i>

10:23.582 --> 10:24.667
Live!

10:24.750 --> 10:27.336
-[Blossom echoing] Live!
<i>-Adieu!</i>

10:28.003 --> 10:29.088
[dogs barking]

10:29.171 --> 10:31.757
Holy shit,
I can't believe she would have eaten me.

10:32.925 --> 10:34.093
Oh, my God.

10:34.176 --> 10:35.803
Is that how you put the dogs down?

10:36.595 --> 10:38.139
Oh, no. We drown them in a bucket.

10:38.222 --> 10:40.891
I just use the shotgun
to keep their heads underwater.

10:40.975 --> 10:42.184
[Bert grunts]

10:42.268 --> 10:44.103
So you gonna take that other pug, too?

10:45.479 --> 10:47.940
Um... uh...

10:48.524 --> 10:50.901
-Uh...
-[Bert] Please, Maria! I need her!

10:52.945 --> 10:54.780
Yes. Yes, yes, yes, yes.

10:54.864 --> 10:56.323
Okay, cool.

10:56.407 --> 10:59.160
[Maria] Okay.
[Bert] I dub thee...

10:59.243 --> 11:00.619
Blueberry.

11:00.703 --> 11:04.331
Blueberry it is.
'Cause you're sweet, and small, and quiet.

11:04.415 --> 11:06.250
Just... like a blueberry.

11:07.668 --> 11:10.546
You know what, guys?
I'm gonna make a quick phone call.

11:13.090 --> 11:14.216
[cell phone ringing]

11:18.888 --> 11:20.639
[Bruce] <i>Salad department. Bruce speaking.</i>

11:20.723 --> 11:21.807
Hey, Bruce. It's Maria.

11:21.891 --> 11:23.475
Would you like to represent me again?

11:23.559 --> 11:24.977
[gasps]

11:25.060 --> 11:26.437
I'm coming home!

11:26.562 --> 11:28.272
Oh, yes!

11:28.355 --> 11:30.024
[Maria] <i>And that's how</i>
<i>I made it back to LA.</i>

11:30.107 --> 11:32.109
<i>I was really throwing myself</i>
<i>into my work</i>

11:32.192 --> 11:33.986
<i>and forgetting about my breakup </i>
<i>with Scott.</i>

11:34.069 --> 11:37.781
Oh, this is so funny.
Putting herpes on someone.

11:37.865 --> 11:40.784
-Normally, I'm covering these things up.
-[both chuckling]

11:40.868 --> 11:41.869
[Bruce] Maria!

11:42.703 --> 11:44.997
-[muffled] Oh! Hey, Bruce!
-[Bruce] How you doin'?

11:45.080 --> 11:46.415
Oh. Sorry.

11:46.498 --> 11:47.625
[clattering]

11:47.708 --> 11:49.043
-[cat meowing]
-Sorry.

11:49.126 --> 11:50.711
-Uh, listen...
-[Maria] Hey.

11:50.794 --> 11:53.881
Please. Uh...
Not a word about my current state, okay?

11:53.964 --> 11:55.633
Believe me, I've heard it all already.

11:56.592 --> 11:58.093
So, uh, how are you?

11:58.177 --> 12:02.097
Good! Yeah...
just glad to be working and...

12:03.307 --> 12:07.311
pushing down all the feelings
down, down, down, about the breakup.

12:08.020 --> 12:09.772
So, do you have anything for me?

12:09.855 --> 12:11.023
I got some great news.

12:11.106 --> 12:14.485
The bladder people, Quandranique,
are looking for another older woman

12:14.568 --> 12:18.030
for a spot where you walk around
holding hands with an animated bladder.

12:18.113 --> 12:20.074
-Lisa Rinna's already on board.
-Oh.

12:20.157 --> 12:21.325
They need you to play somebody who's,

12:21.408 --> 12:24.119
well, more than friends with her
at an outdoor concert.

12:24.203 --> 12:25.621
Yeah, of course. I accept.

12:25.704 --> 12:28.457
I have to say, Maria,
I'm really digging your enthusiasm.

12:28.540 --> 12:29.625
This is just great.

12:29.708 --> 12:32.461
I feel like we're really clicking
like never before.

12:32.544 --> 12:35.673
You're finally getting
the Bruce Ben-Bacharach plan for you.

12:35.756 --> 12:36.590
Take anything.

12:36.674 --> 12:37.591
[chuckling] Yeah!

12:37.675 --> 12:40.135
-Toot, toot!
-Toot, toot!

12:40.219 --> 12:41.220
[both chuckling]

12:41.303 --> 12:42.763
[serene music playing]

12:44.390 --> 12:45.641
