25:40.123 --> 25:41.541
with the knee-jerk breakup.

25:41.624 --> 25:42.625
Okay.

25:43.543 --> 25:45.503
Well, I guess... we're over.

25:45.587 --> 25:50.592
I guess this is how... you have a fight,
and then it's... It ends and...

25:50.675 --> 25:54.888
I... I bid you <i>adieu...</i>
Sweet prince, <i>adieu.</i>

25:54.971 --> 25:56.014
Maria...

25:56.931 --> 26:00.477
You know you can have a fight
with someone and not break up?

26:01.436 --> 26:03.062
-Really?
-Mmm-hmm.

26:03.938 --> 26:07.317
You can't do it every day, but,
every once in a while, for sure.

26:07.400 --> 26:09.068
Even on holidays?

26:09.152 --> 26:10.570
Especially on holidays.

26:11.613 --> 26:13.948
Well, fuck you, then!

26:14.032 --> 26:15.784
[chuckling] Fuck you, too!

26:15.867 --> 26:19.996
[chuckling] So you're not...
You're not mad at me anymore?

26:20.079 --> 26:23.082
Nah... I love you.

26:23.917 --> 26:26.127
Oh, I feel sick!

26:27.253 --> 26:31.466
Blossom said to put my fear behind me...
and to live.

26:32.550 --> 26:34.093
Maybe this is what she was talking about.

26:34.177 --> 26:35.261
Nah.

26:36.179 --> 26:38.723
I think this is what
she was talking about.

26:38.807 --> 26:40.642
[both chuckling]

26:40.725 --> 26:44.020
-That thing isn't real, right?
-No. It's a prosthetic.

26:44.103 --> 26:45.605
[both giggling]

26:49.108 --> 26:50.360
Wow!

26:50.443 --> 26:52.695
-Blossom never kissed me like that.
-[both chuckle]

26:52.779 --> 26:54.864
-Look, I made you something.
-Oh!

26:56.157 --> 26:57.826
-Ready?
-Yes.

26:59.410 --> 27:02.247
[gasps] You painted my vision board.

27:02.330 --> 27:03.915
And I added myself into it.

27:03.998 --> 27:05.750
Is that your tax return?

27:06.543 --> 27:07.585
Yeah. I don't have much.

27:07.669 --> 27:09.796
-Oh, that's okay.
-Mmm.

27:09.879 --> 27:11.130
Is that number what I think it is?

27:11.214 --> 27:14.467
The 410?
That's my credit score.

27:14.551 --> 27:19.180
That is the most intimate thing
a man has ever shared with me.

27:19.264 --> 27:21.933
-Yeah, it's pretty low.
-It is ridiculously low.

27:22.016 --> 27:25.854
And I'm gonna help you get a handle on it.
With workbooks.

27:25.937 --> 27:27.397
-I'd like that.
-[laughing]

27:28.147 --> 27:34.028
I can't believe you painted yourself into
my vision board and drew me to you.

27:34.112 --> 27:35.697
Yeah. And then I drew a pizza.

27:37.282 --> 27:39.075
And that made me hungry,
so I ordered pizza.

27:39.158 --> 27:40.618
-Oh.
-[Bert] Pizza's here?

27:40.702 --> 27:42.078
Hey, Bert.

27:42.161 --> 27:45.915
[Maria] Oh! Bert, what are you doing here?
[Bert] I was watching the game with Scott.

27:45.999 --> 27:48.209
We've also gotten into craft brewing.

27:48.293 --> 27:49.544
Oh!

27:58.469 --> 28:00.930
[Maria chuckling] Okay! Okay.

28:03.057 --> 28:05.184
[Maria] <i>Life.</i>
<i>What a kick in the pants.</i>

28:05.268 --> 28:07.061
<i>Love had come for me after all.</i>

28:07.145 --> 28:09.397
<i>So, what does the future hold?</i>
<i>Who knows?</i>

28:09.480 --> 28:10.648
<i>Who cares?</i>

28:10.732 --> 28:13.735
<i>My hair is blowing and I'm riding</i>
<i>a bicycle above the clouds,</i>

28:13.818 --> 28:15.320
<i>and that's enough.</i>

28:15.403 --> 28:18.740
Now I feel like I'm getting somewhere!
[chuckling]

28:19.657 --> 28:24.913
[choir singing]
<i>♪ I don't know what I'm doing ♪</i>

28:24.996 --> 28:30.627
<i>♪ More than half of the time ♪</i>

28:30.710 --> 28:32.712
[light jazz playing]

